---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ" description="Frequently asked questions about visiting Gurugram.">
  <Hero 
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    subtitle="Everything You Need to Know"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>What is the best time to visit Gurugram?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            The best time to visit Gurugram is from October to March when the weather is pleasant with temperatures ranging from 10-25°C. This period is ideal for sightseeing and outdoor activities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>How do I reach Gurugram from Delhi Airport?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Indira Gandhi International Airport is about 15 km from Gurugram. You can take a taxi/cab (₹500-800), use the metro (Yellow Line to HUDA City Centre), or take an airport express bus. The journey takes approximately 30-45 minutes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>What are the must-visit attractions in Gurugram?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Top attractions include Kingdom of Dreams, Sultanpur National Park, Cyber Hub, Ambience Mall, Damdama Lake, and various historical temples. Check our <a href="/attractions" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Attractions page</a> for a complete list.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>Is Gurugram safe for tourists?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Yes, Gurugram is generally safe for tourists. However, it's advisable to take standard precautions: use registered taxis, avoid isolated areas late at night, keep valuables secure, and follow local customs. See our <a href="/travel-tips" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Travel Tips</a> page for detailed safety information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>What is the local language in Gurugram?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Hindi and English are widely spoken in Gurugram. Haryanvi is the local dialect. Most signs, menus, and official communications are in English, so English-speaking tourists should have no trouble communicating.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>What currency is used in Gurugram?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Indian Rupee (INR) is the currency. Credit and debit cards are widely accepted at hotels, restaurants, and malls. ATMs are easily available. It's recommended to keep some cash for small vendors, auto-rickshaws, and local markets.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>How can I book a guided tour?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            You can book guided tours through our <a href="/tours" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Tours & Guides</a> page. Fill out the booking form or contact us directly via phone or email. We offer various tours including heritage walks, food tours, and nature tours.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>What is the local cuisine like?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Gurugram offers a diverse culinary scene. Traditional Haryanvi cuisine includes dishes like Bajra Roti, Kachri ki Sabzi, and Bathua Raita. The city also has excellent street food and international restaurants. Check our <a href="/food" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Food & Cuisine</a> page for recommendations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>Is there public transportation in Gurugram?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Yes, Gurugram has good public transportation. The Rapid Metro connects various parts of the city and links to the Delhi Metro. City buses, auto-rickshaws, and app-based cabs (Uber, Ola) are also available. See our <a href="/transport" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Transport</a> page for detailed information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>Can I get a local SIM card in Gurugram?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Yes, local SIM cards are available at the airport, mobile stores, and authorized dealers. You'll need valid ID proof (passport for international tourists). 4G and 5G networks are widely available throughout the city.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>What should I wear when visiting temples?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Modest clothing is appreciated when visiting temples. It's recommended to cover your shoulders and knees. You'll also need to remove your shoes before entering temples. Some temples may provide cloth wraps if needed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" style="padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3>Are there any entry fees for attractions?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-top: 1rem;">
            Entry fees vary by attraction. Most temples are free, while parks and entertainment venues may charge entry fees. Check individual attraction pages for current pricing. Some attractions offer discounts for students and senior citizens.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: var(--color-bg-light); border-radius: 0.75rem;">
          <h3>Still have questions?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 1rem 0;">
            Can't find the answer you're looking for? Please get in touch with our friendly team.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>


